article.headline: Duquesne 31, Marist 21
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- Kevin Rombach threw for 329 yards to lead Duquesne to a 31-21 victory over Marist in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference Football League Saturday. Rhombach finished the day 16-of-25 with one interception. He threw for three touchdowns, two of which went to Bruce Hocker. Marist quarterback Stephen McGrath finished 17-of-28 for 220 yards, with no interceptions. Running back Greg Hough had 111 rushing yards on 24 carries for the Dukes (3-2, 1-0). Wide receiver Daniel Dulac caught a career-high two touchdown passes for the Red Foxes (0-6, 0-1). Marek Lapinski scored the first touchdown for Duquesne on a 4-yard running play early in the first quarter. Mark Troyan kicked for the extra point. Duquesne made it 14-0 in the second with a 34-yard touchdown pass from Rombach to Hocker, and another extra point kick by Troyan. Marist got on the board with 3:57 left in the second quarter on a 12-yard touchdown pass from McGrath to Dulac. Duquesne answered 1:05 later with an 85-yard touchdown connection from Rombach to Alex Roberson. Marist scored again two minutes later when McGrath threw Dulac a 39-yard touchdown pass, and Chris Collins kicked for the extra point. Duquesne expanded its lead with a third-quarter field goal by Troyan and a 13-yard touchdown pass from Rombach to Hocker.
